<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 94 / International Company News: Growth at Sun Micro falls short
of expectations
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Sun Microsystems, the US maker of computer work-stations and operating
systems, said revenues in its third quarter were up only slightly from a
year before - well below the 12-15 per cent growth rate generally expected
by analysts.
In a brief statement after the stock market closed on Thursday, Sun said it
estimated that revenues in the period to March 27 were Dollars 1.17-Dollars
1.20bn, compared with Dollars 1.14bn a year earlier.
Sales in the US were held back 'to some extent' by the introduction last
week of new products, which had led some customers to delay purchases, said
Michael Lehman, chief financial officer.
