<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 94 / US accuses Serbs of atrocities
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER and LAURA SILBER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON, BELGRADE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US yesterday accused Serbs of a new wave of ethnic atrocities in
northern Bosnia and called for those guilty of war crimes to be brought to
justice. It said Serbs were trying to drive out Moslems, Croats and gypsies
from the towns of Banja Luka and Prijedor. The US condemnation follows
United Nations and Red Cross reports accusing Serbs of murdering 17 Moslems
and two Croats in the Prijedor area, although Serb police claimed they were
investigating only seven deaths.
Meanwhile, the UN is considering despatch of 800 Ukrainian peacekeepers to
Gorazde, the besieged Moslem enclave in eastern Bosnia. This move comes as
Serb attacks on Gorazde have left 30 people dead and 132 wounded since
Monday. Serb media, however, claimed a Moslem offensive was under way.
The UN is also considering sending reinforcements for the French
peacekeeping contingent in the north-western Moslem area of Bihac, where
Serb and Bosnian forces yesterday signed a ceasefire. Plans for bolstering
peacekeeping forces in Bosnia follow approval by the UN Security Council on
Thursday of an extra 3,700 troops and advisers.
</TEXT>
