<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 94 / Japan reactor near critical level
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A nuclear chain reaction will reach a critical, self-sustaining level next
Tuesday in Japan's controversial 'fast-breeder' nuclear reactor, officials
said yesterday. The fast-breeder reactor uses plutonium as a base substance
to generate electric power. Other industrialised nations have dropped plans
for fast-breeders because of the hazards associated with plutonium, leaving
Japan as the only country actively pursuing the technology as an energy
source. The plant, is located in Tsuruga, Fukui Prefecture, 335 km west of
Tokyo.
</TEXT>
