FT  02 APR 94 / Markets: Insurer retrains agents - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Norwich Union, one of the UK's leading insurers, this week suspended 800
agents, including its entire life and pensions direct sales force for a
month, for retraining. The move was prompted by Lautro, the life insurance
industry's self-regulatory organisation.
