<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 94 / London Stock Exchange: Equity futures and options trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TERRY BYLAND
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Derivatives markets shared in the volatility seen in equity sectors in the
final pre-Easter trading session, writes Terry Byland. For much of the day,
the June contract on the Footsie traded at a small discount to the cash
market but traders stressed that dealing was restrained.
The final reading of 3,058 showed the contract at a substantial discount to
the cash market but some ground was recovered in after hours trading.
Trading volume was swollen to just over 15,000 contracts in the June
contract.
