FT  02 APR 94 / UK Company News: De-listing fear for London Securities
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
London Securities, the property investment company, has warned that if
ongoing discussions for the completion of a property purchase are not
completed by the end of this month the company would be threatened with
de-listing.
London Securities completed a company voluntary arrangement in 1992, whereby
its previous assets were put under the control of its secured lenders,
leaving the company as a cash shell.
It is considering the purchase of properties from its Nu-Swift, the fire
protection and property group which with a 29 per cent stake is the
company's largest shareholder.
It yesterday announced a pre-tax loss of Pounds 342,000 for the year to
September 30 1993, reflecting the absence of operating businesses. Losses
per share were 0.6p.
