FT  02 APR 94 / Coal-fired power stations to close
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
National Power is to close up to five coal-fired power stations in the next
12 months with the loss of 270 to 410 jobs. It will mothball three oil-fired
generating units immediately.
It is closing Rugeley A in Staffordshire, Skelton Grange in Leeds, and
Willington A near Derby from September 30.
It expects to close Aberthaw A, South Glamorgan, and Uskmouth, Gwent, in a
year.
It has mothballed one oil-fired unit at each of Fawley, Southampton,
Littlebrook, Kent, and Pembroke, Dyfed.
