peacekeeping contingent in Bihac, in Bosnia's north-western Moslem area,
where Serb and Bosnian forces yesterday signed a ceasefire, said a senior UN
official. The plans for bolstering the peacekeeping forces in Bosnia follows
approval by the UN Security Council on Thursday of an extra 3,700 troops and
advisers.
