<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 94 / International Company News: TWA reduces losses after
cut-back
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TWA, the US airline which emerged from bankruptcy last November, narrowed
its operating losses to Dollars 281.3m last year, from Dollars 404.6m in
1992, as it cut back the scale of its operations.
However, a Dollars 342m pension fund charge, offset by some items resulting
from the company's reorganisation, led it to report a pre-tax loss (before
extraordinary items) of Dollars 450.8m, compared with Dollars 342m in 1992.
</TEXT>
